it.polimi.constraints.reachability

Class ReachabilityEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.constraints.reachability.ReachabilityEntry

  • public class ReachabilityEntry
extends Object
    Contains a reachability entry. The reachability entry specifies the reachability between an incoming and an outgoing transition of a sub-property, i.e., if an incoming transition transition can be reached from an outgoing transition in the intersection automaton
    Author:
    Claudio Menghi

    • Constructor Detail

      • ReachabilityEntry

        public ReachabilityEntry(LabeledPluggingTransition incomingTransition,
                 LabeledPluggingTransition outgoingTransition,
                 boolean modelAccepting,
                 boolean claimAccepting)
        creates a new reachability entry
        Parameters:
        incomingTransition - is the incoming transition reachable from the outgoing transition of the sub-property
        outgoingTransition - is the outgoing transition
        modelAccepting - is true if there is an accepting state for the model in one of the runs that connect the incoming and outgoing transition
        claimAccepting - is true if there is an accepting state for the claim in one of the runs that connect the incoming and outgoing transition
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the incoming or the outgoing transition is null
